LEGIONELLA - UNITED KINGDOM (2)
===============================
The status of Legionellosis in the U.K. (quoted from GIDEON software):
1,898 cases reported for England and Wales during 1980 to 1989 (240 fatal
= 12.6%); 188 in 1990; 111 in 1991; 147 in 1992 - Trent, Western
Midlands, Yorkshire and Southeast Thames accounted for 50% of reports);
129 in 1993 (22 fatal); 160 in 1994 (56% associated with local or foreign
travel); 218 hospital-associated cases reported during 1980 to 1992
23 cases reported in Scotland in 1990; 29 in 1992; 17 in 1993; 13 in 1994
0 cases reported in Northern Ireland in 1990; 1 in 1991;
2 in 1992; 1 in 1993.
--
Prof. Berger
e-mail: mberger@post.tau.ac.il
